Class TreeMap

java.lang.Object

                  TreeMap
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable
public class TreeMap
extends prefuse.Display

This class is responsible for creating a TreeMap visualisation of the given dataset. The Tree which it visualises is structured as follows: - The first level contains the name of the states - Each state has as its children the political parties in that state, as the second level of the tree - Each political party has as its children the MPs in of that political party from the state, as the third level of the tree The nodes corresponding to MPs are color coded according to the political parties to which they belong, with the same color for a given party across all states.
